def: To carry burdens in a cart; to follow the business of a carter.

An ornament, gem, or scroll, or a package containing a relic,etc., worn as a charm or preservative against evils or mischief, suchas diseases and witchcraft, and generally inscribed with mystic formsor characters.
Having eighteen leaves to a sheet; as, an octodecimo form,book, leaf, size, etc.
Pertaining to allodium; freehold; free of rent or service; heldindependent of a lord paramount; -- opposed to feudal; as, allodiallands; allodial system. Blackstone.
Having all the toes turned forward, as the colies.
A French cordial or liqueur flavored with anise seeds. DeColange.
Accustomedness; habit; habitual use.Assuetude of things hurtful doth make them lose their force to hurt.Bacon.
One who, or that which, punches.
Pertaining to the dermis or true skin.
The act of one who spells; formation of words by letters;orthography.
